HEADWORD: Self-indulgence
<hw>Self`-in*dul"gence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Indulgence
of one's appetites, desires, or inclinations; -- the opposite of
<ant>self-restraint</ant>, and <ant>self-denial</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-indulgent</ent>⟦br⟧
